This paper discusses the design of a secure pairing protocol for IoT devices, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The protocol uses wireless communication, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of on-board clocks and power supply chargers also suggests a possible connection to embedded systems (cs.EM) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper includes experiments and user studies, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) if the data collected is used to train models.
